                                <div class="attribute-header">
                                    <h1>Mobile Web: a growing market</h1>
                                </div>

                                <div class="attribute-byline">
				    <div><a href="http://ez.no/About-eZ/Events-News/News/Mobile-Web-a-growing-market">Read Original Item</a></div><br />
                                </div>

                                <div class="attribute-byline">
                                    <p class="date">01/07/2013 06:58 am</p>
                                    <p class="author">info@ez.no (Charles Clement-Cottuz)</p>
				                                    </div>

				

				<div class="attribute-body float-break">
				      <p><b>To what extent are the Open Source Content Management Systems (CMS) that are already available on the market, suitable for the creation of mobile websites?</b></p><p><b>Christof Zahneissen:</b> Basically, all Open Source CMS can be used to create mobile websites - but by no means can all support a mobile-first strategy effectively. In many regions, more and more people turn to the Internet through mobile end devices rather than through stationary equipment. Therefore many industries are currently changing and need to adapt their business models dramatically to the massive increase in mobile access rates.</p><p>An elaborate Mobile Strategy is absolutely essential for businesses, due to the diversity of cross-media usage scenarios. We are pursuing a clear mobile-first focus and offer solutions from the support of <a href="/Products/Demos-Videos/eZ-Publish-Enterprise-Responsive-Design-Demo" target="_self">Responsive Design</a> over the so-called <a href="/Products/eZ-Market/Explore-the-eZ-Market/eZ-App-Factory" target="_self">App Factory</a>, up to the creation of native Apps. In addition, we are intensely dealing with the topic of video streaming to mobile devices, which will be the next main topic in the media industry.</p><p><b>How complex is the creation of mobile websites with Open Source CMS solutions?</b></p><p><b>Zahneissen:</b> It very much depends on the approach that was chosen: HTML pages, based on the responsive design approach, can be implemented more cost-effective and faster than native apps for iOS, Android or Windows Mobile. <a href="/Products/Demos-Videos/eZ-Publish-Enterprise-Responsive-Design-Demo" target="_self">Responsive design</a> means that the representation of the contents adjusts automatically on each screen area. Therefore web administrators must ask always, what is important in the current context - from the creation of texts to the point of delivery to mobile devices. The abilities of the content management system always have to be evaluated exactly.</p><p><b>Where should a company that wants to perform the creation of mobile websites on its own, find the right employees, in view of the prevailing shortage of skilled workers in the mobility environment?</b></p><p><b>Zahneissen:</b> Finding the right professionals is a difficult task, especially when both, expertise in CMS and in the mobility environment, are required. One can therefore circumvent the skills shortage by utilizing solutions that create apps at the push of a button. With the <a href="/Products/eZ-Market/Explore-the-eZ-Market/eZ-App-Factory" target="_self">App Factory</a>, we offer an integrated tool that arranges apps through drag and drop, and compiles all popular mobile operating systems, at the push of a button. Like this, mobile solutions can be implemented and distributed, without the usually necessary technical expertise.</p><p><b>Currently everybody is talking about the edition of content to mobile devices. But how "mobile" is actually the back end? To what extent can editors already make changes, releases or updates by using a smartphone or tablet?</b></p><p><b>Zahneissen:</b> We are following a so-called <i>Touch First Strategy:</i> Operation via touch screen is the first priority while all other user interfaces will be developed on that basis. The first mobile backend for editors is already in the testing phase and will be released with a future version. Members of <a href="/Community" target="_self">our community</a> with more than 43,000 professionals can test the backend currently before its official release.</p><p><b>How comfortable is the mobile work?</b><b>&nbsp;</b></p><p><b>Zahneissen: </b>Everyone who creates and manages websites can confirm that mobile work makes sense for simple tasks only. Therefore, our focus is on the processing of approvals, on the verification and correction of content or elements, tests, <a href="/Products/eZ-Market/Explore-the-eZ-Market/eZ-odoscope" target="_self">Website analysis</a> and system monitoring. Together with our community, we have developed promising ideas for the mobile back-end, in whose implementation we are currently investigating.</p><div class="separator"><span></span></div><p><i>In: </i><b>Mobile Websites</b></p><p><i>Source:</i><a href="http://www.mobilebusiness.de/home/newsdetails/article/videostreams-im-kommen.html" target="_self"><b>http://www.mobilebusiness.de/home/newsdetails/article/videostreams-im-kommen.html</b></a></p>
				</div>

                                
